==English==
===Intransitive verb===
'''[[come]] [[across]]'''
#{{idiom}} To give an [[appearance]] or [[impression]]; to project a certain [[image]].
#:''A business suit and briefcase help her to '''come across''' as the competent professional she is.''

===Transitive verb===
'''come across'''
#{{idiom}} To [[find]], [[encounter]] or [[discover]].
#:''If you '''come across''' any stores that still carry the discontinued style, please let me know.''

